Have you heard or said any of these?

  • Can you show me how you did that?
  • Can you share the code?
  • I dont understand what you did.
  • I would like to build upon that.
  • I think that would be a great way to do XXXX

What is it?

Reproducible analysis means that data analyses are documented with their data and code so that others may verify the methods and findings and also enhance or build upon them. This provides transparency, which is the foundation of effective analysis underpinning both validity and reproducibility.

Why it is important

  • Collaboration with others
  • Documentation
  • Re-use

How to do it using R

  • Sweave does this with LaTeX
  • knitr builds on Sweave
  • Can use Python, Awk, Ruby, Haskell, Bash, Perl, Graphviz, TikZ, SAS, Scala, and CoffeeScript.
  • An explanation of the program logic in a natural language, interspersed with snippets of code.
  • Donald Knuth introduced literate programming to allow programmers to develop programs in the order demanded by the logic and flow of their thoughts rather than the needs of the computer.

Submitting to DSCOE

  1. Have a great idea
  2. Have something to share with the community (DoD)
  3. Write a tutorial clearly explaining your idea.
  4. Put it in the DSCOE format (https://github.com/iankloo/dscoemarkdown)
  5. Submit it
  6. Be prepared receive gracious gifts from random people.
